Pop a #baking tray{} in the oven and heat your oven to 200 degrees. Peel the @celeriac{1} with a sharp #knife{} and cut in half. Cut into ½ cm slices and then cut each slice again lengthways at ½ cm intervals to create skinny celeriac fries.

Put the celeriac fries on the pre-heated baking tray, toss with @oil{1%tbsp} and @salt{1/4%tsp}, and pop on the top shelf of the oven for ~{30%minutes}, or until the fries are crispy and golden. Turn halfway.

In the meantime, finely chop the @garlic{1%clove} and the @flat leaf parsley{3}, pick the @thyme{1.5} leaves off the sprigs, zest and juice a quarter of the @lemon{1} and smash the @walnuts{3} into very small pieces. Combine these ingredients in a #large bowl{}, together with @olive oil{2%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{a good grind}.

Slice your @chestnut mushrooms{1} into ½ cm pieces, add to the bowl and mix everything together. Transfer the mixture to another baking tray, spreading it in an even layer.

Place the @salmon fillet{2} on top, skin-side down. Move the celeriac to the middle shelf of the oven and put the salmon on the top shelf of the oven for ~{15%minutes}.

> The salmon is cooked when it is opaque throughout.

Serve the salmon on top of the walnut-herby mushrooms and garnish with any remaining parsley and a wedge of lemon. Serve with a side of celeriac fries.